HEADWORD: Hypsometry
<hw>Hyp*som"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That branch of
the science of geodesy which has to do with the measurement of heights,
either absolutely with reference to the sea level, or
relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypsiprymnodon</ent>⟦br⟧
